  <bioghist audience="internal" id="aspace_9a478dd4c978e76b2593c2cf4ae568bc">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>Resident Director, Ecology House; Director of Robert Purcell Union; Associate Dean and Director of Willard Straight Hall, Cornell University, 1976-1993. Director of HIV Counseling and Testing, Whitman-Walker Clinic in Washington,DC, 2000-2004.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_8e5d6dbbd7bbf571914cdb7c57531f6e">
    <head>Scope and content</head>
<p>Correspondence, subject files, audiocassettes, and other materials documenting the shift from gay liberation to gay and lesbian activism, and concerning the establishment of organizations, programs, and issues at Cornell and in Ithaca, including the Cornell University Library's Human Sexuality Collection, Ithaca's Fair Practice Ordinance, the adoption of Tompkins County's Local Law C, the addition of sexual orientation to the University's Equal Opportunity statement, and the development of AIDS awareness and and an AIDS policy at Cornell.  Also files on sexuality-related and men's conferences, 1985-91 and on the Ithaca Alternative Spiritual Community, and additional files on Ellis' professional and activist life.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <userestrict audience="internal" id="aspace_b5dc13e40097475cc06fefb07120e2f6">
    <head>Restrictions on Use:</head>
<p>Due to the fragility and potential degradation of moving image and sound recordings, viewing and listening is limited to items that have been digitized. If an item is in another media format, you may request to have the item digitized for access. Information on ordering access copies may be found on the Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections webpage.</p>  </userestrict>
  <userestrict audience="internal" id="aspace_2515697c3ccf105e33ba5c7f798431ee">
    <head>Restrictions on Use:</head>
<p>Audio visual media that has been digitized: TR-17118 to TR-17122.</p>  </userestrict>
